  "text": "For the evaluation of RBBF, data from samples containing 400 spheres are presented in order to ascertain the validity of the measurement [CITATION_1] . Mean arterial blood pressure ranged between 64 B 13 (5th injection) and 71 B 12 mm Hg (2nd injection) but did not change significantly throughout the experiments. Renal blood flow values remained between 2.5 B 0.9 and 2.9 B 0.4 ml/min/g. No significant differences were observed between the individual injections and between blood flow values of left and right kidney. Blood flow values of the tibial condyle (6.6 B 1.1 to 8.5 B 1.4 ml/min/100 g) and femoral condyle (4.3 B 1.1 to 6.0 B 1.1 ml/min/100 g) were not different between the various time intervals during the experiments (fig. 2) . The RBBF of the femoral condyle was significantly lower than that of the tibial condyle at each time point (fig. 2) . The blood flow of the medial tibial condyle was between 8.0 B 2.2 and 10.8 B 2.0 ml/ min/100 g and slightly higher than that of the lateral tibial condyle (between 7.5 B 1.6 and 9.0 B 2.2 ml/min/100 g). However, these differences were statistically not significant. The medial and lateral femoral condyle blood flow values varied between 5.5 B 1.5 and 6.8 B 1.6, and 3.8 B 1.4 and 5.2 B 0.3 ml/min/100 g, respectively ( fig. 3 ).",
